{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LuRbJbujTxnv4adbxPryNB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8.3: cargo-tarpaulin coverage detection and parsing\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running coverage on a Rust project,\n     8→I want codeharness to detect cargo-tarpaulin, run it, and parse the JSON report,\n     9→so that coverage metrics are tracked at parity with Node.js/Python.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given a Rust project with `cargo-tarpaulin` installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin', runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/', reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given a Rust workspace project (Cargo.toml contains `[workspace]`), when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then the run command includes `--workspace` flag <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC3: Given a `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json` file with `\"coverage\": 85.5`, when `parseCoverageReport()` is called with format `'tarpaulin-json'`, then it returns `85.5` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC4: Given `cargo test` output containing `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored`, when `parseTestCounts()` is called, then it returns `{ passCount: 42, failCount: 3 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC5: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is NOT installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called on a Rust project, then it returns `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    20→\n    21→- [x] Task 1: Update `detectCoverageTool()` rust branch in coverage.ts (AC: #1, #2, #5)\n    22→  - [x] 1.1 Add `cargo-tarpaulin` installation check via `cargo tarpaulin --version` subprocess\n    23→  - [x] 1.2 Return `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with warning if tarpaulin not installed\n    24→  - [x] 1.3 Update `runCommand` to `'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/'`\n    25→  - [x] 1.4 Add workspace detection: read Cargo.toml for `[workspace]` section, append `--workspace` if present\n    26→- [x] Task 2: Add `tarpaulin-json` branch to `parseCoverageReport()` (AC: #3)\n    27→  - [x] 2.1 Create `parseTarpaulinCoverage(dir)` function\n    28→  - [x] 2.2 Read `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json`, extract top-level `\"coverage\"` field\n    29→  - [x] 2.3 Wire into `parseCoverageReport()` format switch\n    30→- [x] Task 3: Add `cargo test` output parsing to `parseTestCounts()` (AC: #4)\n    31→  - [x] 3.1 Add regex for `test result: ok. N passed; N failed; N ignored` format\n    32→  - [x] 3.2 Handle both `ok` and `FAILED` result lines\n    33→- [x] Task 4: Write unit tests for all new code paths\n    34→  - [x] 4.1 Tests for detectCoverageTool rust with tarpaulin installed vs not installed\n    35→  - [x] 4.2 Tests for workspace flag inclusion\n    36→  - [x] 4.3 Tests for parseTarpaulinCoverage with valid/invalid/missing report\n    37→  - [x] 4.4 Tests for parseTestCounts with cargo test output format (ok and FAILED)\n    38→- [x] Task 5: Run full test suite — zero regressions\n    39→\n    40→## Dev Notes\n    41→\n    42→### Current State of Rust Coverage Code\n    43→\n    44→Story 8-2 already added a rust branch to `detectCoverageTool()` in `src/lib/coverage.ts` (lines 51-57). It is a stub that needs replacement:\n    45→\n    46→```typescript\n    47→// CURRENT (incomplete — from 8-2 code review fix)\n    48→if (stack === 'rust') {\n    49→  return {\n    50→    tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    51→    runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json',\n    52→    reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json',\n    53→  };\n    54→}\n    55→```\n    56→\n    57→**Problems with current code:**\n    58→1. No tarpaulin install check — unconditionally returns `cargo-tarpaulin` (violates AC #5)\n    59→2. Wrong `runCommand` — missing `--output-dir coverage/` (violates AC #1)\n    60→3. No workspace detection — missing `--workspace` flag (violates AC #2)\n    61→4. `parseCoverageReport()` has no `tarpaulin-json` branch — falls through to `return 0` (violates AC #3)\n    62→5. `parseTestCounts()` has no cargo test regex (violates AC #4)\n    63→\n    64→### Implementation Guide\n    65→\n    66→**All changes in single file: `src/lib/coverage.ts`**\n    67→\n    68→#### 1. Replace rust branch in detectCoverageTool (lines 51-57)\n    69→\n    70→```typescript\n    71→if (stack === 'rust') {\n    72→  // Check if cargo-tarpaulin is installed\n    73→  try {\n    74→    execSync('cargo tarpaulin --version', { stdio: 'pipe', timeout: 10_000 });\n    75→  } catch {\n    76→    warn('cargo-tarpaulin not installed — coverage detection unavailable');\n    77→    return { tool: 'unknown', runCommand: '', reportFormat: '' };\n    78→  }\n    79→\n    80→  // Detect workspace\n    81→  const cargoPath = join(baseDir, 'Cargo.toml');\n    82→  let isWorkspace = false;\n    83→  try {\n    84→    const cargoContent = readFileSync(cargoPath, 'utf-8');\n    85→    isWorkspace = /^\\[workspace\\]/m.test(cargoContent);\n    86→  } catch { /* not a workspace */ }\n    87→\n    88→  const wsFlag = isWorkspace ? ' --workspace' : '';\n    89→  return {\n    90→    tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    91→    runCommand: `cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/${wsFlag}`,\n    92→    reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json',\n    93→  };\n    94→}\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→`execSync` is already imported at line 1. `readFileSync` and `join` are already imported.\n    98→\n    99→#### 2. Add tarpaulin-json to parseCoverageReport (around line 272)\n   100→\n   101→In `parseCoverageReport()`, add before the `return 0` fallthrough:\n   102→\n   103→```typescript\n   104→if (format === 'tarpaulin-json') {\n   105→  return parseTarpaulinCoverage(dir);\n   106→}\n   107→```\n   108→\n   109→New function (place near other parse functions around line 314):\n   110→\n   111→```typescript\n   112→function parseTarpaulinCoverage(dir: string): number {\n   113→  const reportPath = join(dir, 'coverage', 'tarpaulin-report.json');\n   114→  if (!existsSync(reportPath)) {\n   115→    warn('Tarpaulin report not found at coverage/tarpaulin-report.json');\n   116→    return 0;\n   117→  }\n   118→  try {\n   119→    const report = JSON.parse(readFileSync(reportPath, 'utf-8')) as { coverage?: number };\n   120→    return report.coverage ?? 0;\n   121→  } catch {\n   122→    warn('Failed to parse tarpaulin coverage report');\n   123→    return 0;\n   124→  }\n   125→}\n   126→```\n   127→\n   128→#### 3. Add cargo test regex to parseTestCounts (around line 344)\n   129→\n   130→Add before the final `return { passCount: 0, failCount: 0 }`:\n   131→\n   132→```typescript\n   133→// cargo test format: \"test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored\"\n   134→const cargoMatch = /test result:.*?(\\d+)\\s+passed;\\s*(\\d+)\\s+failed/i.exec(output);\n   135→if (cargoMatch) {\n   136→  return {\n   137→    passCount: parseInt(cargoMatch[1], 10),\n   138→    failCount: parseInt(cargoMatch[2], 10),\n   139→  };\n   140→}\n   141→```\n   142→\n   143→### Tarpaulin Report Format\n   144→\n   145→```json\n   146→{\n   147→  \"coverage\": 85.5,\n   148→  \"files\": [\n   149→    { \"path\": \"src/main.rs\", \"covered\": 10, \"coverable\": 12 }\n   150→  ]\n   151→}\n   152→```\n   153→\n   154→Only the top-level `\"coverage\"` field is needed (float 0-100).\n   155→\n   156→### Cargo Test Output Formats\n   157→\n   158→```\n   159→test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 1.23s\n   160→test result: FAILED. 10 passed; 2 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out\n   161→```\n   162→\n   163→The regex `test result:.*?(\\d+)\\s+passed;\\s*(\\d+)\\s+failed` handles both.\n   164→\n   165→### Architecture Constraints\n   166→\n   167→- **<300 line limit**: `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (pre-existing violation). Adding ~40 lines is acceptable — follow existing pattern, don't refactor file structure in this story.\n   168→- **No new npm dependencies**: All parsing uses `JSON.parse`, regex, and `execSync` (already imported).\n   169→- **NFR4 from epics**: Cargo.toml parsing uses regex, not a TOML parser. Same approach as `stack-detect.ts`.\n   170→- **Result<T> pattern**: `detectCoverageTool` returns `CoverageToolInfo` directly (existing convention). Do not change return type.\n   171→\n   172→### Testing Patterns\n   173→\n   174→Follow existing test patterns in `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`:\n   175→- `mkdtempSync` for temp directories, `rmSync` in `afterEach`\n   176→- Write `Cargo.toml` and `tarpaulin-report.json` fixtures to temp dir\n   177→- For tarpaulin install check: use `vi.spyOn` on child_process `execSync` or use `vi.mock`\n   178→- Existing tests mock at the filesystem level, not at the function level\n   179→\n   180→### Do NOT Duplicate\n   181→\n   182→These were already done in story 8-2 (code review fixes):\n   183→- `CoverageToolInfo.tool` union already includes `'cargo-tarpaulin'`\n   184→- `getDefaultState()` returns `'cargo-tarpaulin'` for rust stack\n   185→- `getStackLabel()` returns `'Rust (Cargo.toml)'` for rust\n   186→- `generateAgentsMdContent()` handles rust stack\n   187→- `getCoverageTool()` in docs-scaffold.ts returns `'cargo-tarpaulin'` for rust\n   188→\n   189→### References\n   190→\n   191→- [Source: src/lib/coverage.ts — detectCoverageTool L35-61, parseCoverageReport L265-273, parseTestCounts L316-345]\n   192→- [Source: src/lib/stack-detect.ts — workspace pattern regex from getCargoDepsSection L70-77]\n   193→- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts — test patterns, mkdtempSync fixtures]\n   194→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md — FR7, FR8, FR9]\n   195→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust.md — previous story learnings]\n   196→\n   197→### Previous Story Intelligence (8-2)\n   198→\n   199→- The rust branch in `detectCoverageTool` was added as a code review fix — it's a stub that this story replaces.\n   200→- Test suite was at 2968 tests after 8-2. Zero regressions expected.\n   201→- Code review in 8-2 found that `detectCoverageTool` originally had no rust branch at all (fell through to unknown). The fix was minimal — this story completes it.\n   202→\n   203→### Git Intelligence\n   204→\n   205→Recent commits: d6a76bf (8-2 verified), 9ddd65e (8-2 AC2 fix), 4c7f498 (8-1 detection).\n   206→Files modified: `state.ts`, `coverage.ts`, `stack-detect.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts` + tests.\n   207→\n   208→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   209→## Verification Requirements\n   210→\n   211→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.proof.md`)\n   212→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   213→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   214→\n   215→## Documentation Requirements\n   216→\n   217→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   218→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.md`\n   219→\n   220→## Testing Requirements\n   221→\n   222→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   223→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   224→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   225→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   226→\n   227→## Dev Agent Record\n   228→\n   229→### Agent Model Used\n   230→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   231→\n   232→### Debug Log References\n   233→N/A\n   234→\n   235→### Completion Notes List\n   236→- Replaced stub rust branch in detectCoverageTool with tarpaulin install check, workspace detection, correct runCommand\n   237→- Added parseTarpaulinCoverage function and wired into parseCoverageReport\n   238→- Added cargo test output regex to parseTestCounts (placed before pytest regex to avoid false match)\n   239→- Added 11 new tests (67 total in coverage.test.ts, 2979 total suite)\n   240→- Used vi.mock('node:child_process') with importOriginal to mock execSync for ESM compatibility\n   241→- Zero regressions across full test suite\n   242→\n   243→### File List\n   244→- src/lib/coverage.ts (modified: detectCoverageTool rust branch, parseCoverageReport tarpaulin-json, parseTarpaulinCoverage new, parseTestCounts cargo regex)\n   245→- src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts (modified: 12 new tests for AC1-AC5 + workspace aggregation)\n   246→- src/lib/AGENTS.md (modified: updated coverage.ts description to include cargo-tarpaulin)\n   247→\n   248→## Senior Developer Review (AI)\n   249→\n   250→**Reviewer:** Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   251→**Date:** 2026-03-23\n   252→\n   253→### Findings Summary\n   254→- 1 HIGH fixed, 1 MEDIUM fixed (AGENTS.md), 1 MEDIUM deferred (proof doc — out of scope for code review)\n   255→\n   256→### HIGH — Fixed: Workspace cargo test count aggregation\n   257→`parseTestCounts()` used `.exec()` which only captures the first `test result:` line. For workspace projects, `cargo test` emits one line per crate. Changed to `matchAll`-style loop with global regex to sum all crate counts. Added test for multi-crate output (18 passed, 3 failed across 3 crates).\n   258→\n   259→### MEDIUM — Fixed: AGENTS.md stale for coverage module\n   260→`src/lib/AGENTS.md` listed coverage.ts tools as \"(Vitest/c8/coverage.py)\" — updated to include cargo-tarpaulin.\n   261→\n   262→### MEDIUM — Not fixed: Missing Showboat proof document\n   263→No proof doc at `docs/exec-plans/active/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.proof.md`. This is created during verification, not code review.\n   264→\n   265→### Verification\n   266→- 2980 tests pass (was 2979, +1 workspace aggregation test), zero regressions\n   267→- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` passes: all 123 files above 80% floor, overall 97%\n   268→- All 5 ACs verified against implementation\n   269→\n   270→### Outcome: Approved with fixes applied → status set to `verifying`\n   271→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012NCb8jmuC161JN1KxhvDkE","session_id":"b2eefe49-15c3-4418-957c-7920103cee96","uuid":"e1b496e2-e127-4e8a-8322-af5ca0d7c7d5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:23:28.338Z"}
