{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GDPtyj9tNeGp3kGwd9Hhc7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-4: Register cargo-tarpaulin in Dependency Registry\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer initializing codeharness on a Rust project,\n     8→I want cargo-tarpaulin to be auto-installed if missing,\n     9→So that coverage works out of the box.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is not installed, when `codeharness init` runs on a Rust project, then it attempts `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given the dependency registry, when checked for `cargo-tarpaulin`, then it has `critical: false`, install command `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin`, check command `cargo tarpaulin --version` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→### Dependency Registry Entry\n    19→\n    20→File: `src/lib/deps.ts` — `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` array.\n    21→\n    22→Add entry following the exact pattern of existing entries (showboat, agent-browser, beads, semgrep):\n    23→\n    24→```typescript\n    25→{\n    26→  name: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    27→  displayName: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    28→  installCommands: [{ cmd: 'cargo', args: ['install', 'cargo-tarpaulin'] }],\n    29→  checkCommand: { cmd: 'cargo', args: ['tarpaulin', '--version'] },\n    30→  critical: false,\n    31→}\n    32→```\n    33→\n    34→### Conditional Installation\n    35→\n    36→This dependency is only relevant for Rust projects. The init pipeline should only attempt installation when the detected stack is `'rust'`. Check how existing stack-conditional dependency installation works in `src/commands/init.ts` or `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — cargo-tarpaulin should follow the same pattern.\n    37→\n    38→If `cargo` is not available on the system, the install will fail gracefully since `critical: false`.\n    39→\n    40→### Tests\n    41→\n    42→File: `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`\n    43→\n    44→Follow the pattern established by story 7-1 (Semgrep registry entry). Add test cases:\n    45→- Registry contains `cargo-tarpaulin` entry\n    46→- `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` length increased by 1\n    47→- Check-installed, install-success, install-failure paths for cargo-tarpaulin\n    48→\n    49→## Files to Change\n    50→\n    51→- `src/lib/deps.ts` — Add `cargo-tarpaulin` entry to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` array\n    52→- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` — Add test coverage for cargo-tarpaulin registry entry (check-installed, install-success, install-failure)\n    53→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012NCb8jmuC161JN1KxhvDkE","session_id":"b2eefe49-15c3-4418-957c-7920103cee96","uuid":"7f906897-746e-447b-b442-e60ba6eb5b3c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:24:03.807Z"}
