{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01M6JXRACSE5P45FtVgiH6Rv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8.4: Register cargo-tarpaulin in dependency registry\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer initializing codeharness on a Rust project,\n    10→I want cargo-tarpaulin to be registered in the dependency registry and auto-installed if missing,\n    11→so that coverage works out of the box without manual setup.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→- [x] AC1: Given the dependency registry in `src/lib/deps.ts`, when inspected for `cargo-tarpaulin`, then it has `critical: false`, install command `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin`, and check command `cargo tarpaulin --version` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC2: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is not installed and `cargo` is available, when `installDependency()` is called with the cargo-tarpaulin spec, then it runs `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` and verifies installation via `cargo tarpaulin --version` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [x] AC3: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is already installed, when `installDependency()` is called with the cargo-tarpaulin spec, then it returns `{ status: 'already-installed' }` without attempting reinstall <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [x] AC4: Given `cargo` is not available on the system, when `installDependency()` is called with the cargo-tarpaulin spec, then it returns `{ status: 'failed' }` gracefully (not critical, does not abort init) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [x] AC5: Given `codeharness init` runs on a Rust project where `cargo-tarpaulin` is not installed, when the dependency install phase executes, then it attempts `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` as part of the normal registry iteration <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    20→\n    21→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    22→\n    23→- [x] Task 1: Add cargo-tarpaulin entry to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` in `src/lib/deps.ts` (AC: #1)\n    24→  - [x] 1.1 Add new `DependencySpec` object after the `bats` entry\n    25→  - [x] 1.2 Set `name: 'cargo-tarpaulin'`, `displayName: 'cargo-tarpaulin'`\n    26→  - [x] 1.3 Set `installCommands: [{ cmd: 'cargo', args: ['install', 'cargo-tarpaulin'] }]` (single command, no fallback)\n    27→  - [x] 1.4 Set `checkCommand: { cmd: 'cargo', args: ['tarpaulin', '--version'] }`\n    28→  - [x] 1.5 Set `critical: false`\n    29→- [x] Task 2: Update existing tests that assert on registry length (AC: #1)\n    30→  - [x] 2.1 Update `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` length assertion from `5` to `6` in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` line 479\n    31→  - [x] 2.2 Update `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` names assertion to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'` in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` line 469\n    32→  - [x] 2.3 Update any `installAllDependencies` tests that depend on exact registry contents (check mock expectations that enumerate all deps)\n    33→- [x] Task 3: Add cargo-tarpaulin-specific tests in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n    34→  - [x] 3.1 Add `describe('cargo-tarpaulin entry')` block following semgrep/bats test pattern\n    35→  - [x] 3.2 Test: returns already-installed when `cargo tarpaulin --version` succeeds\n    36→  - [x] 3.3 Test: installs via `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` and returns installed\n    37→  - [x] 3.4 Test: returns failed when `cargo` command not found (graceful failure)\n    38→  - [x] 3.5 Test: cargo-tarpaulin is not critical\n    39→  - [x] 3.6 Test: has single install command via cargo\n    40→  - [x] 3.7 Test: check command is `cargo tarpaulin --version`\n    41→- [x] Task 4: Update `installAllDependencies` test mocks that enumerate deps by name (AC: #4)\n    42→  - [x] 4.1 In the \"continues when non-critical dep fails\" test (~line 320), add mock handling for `cargo` command\n    43→  - [x] 4.2 In the \"prints FAIL and info messages\" test (~line 438), add mock handling for `cargo` command\n    44→- [x] Task 5: Run full test suite — zero regressions\n    45→\n    46→## Dev Notes\n    47→\n    48→### Registry Structure\n    49→\n    50→The `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` in `src/lib/deps.ts` (line 25) is a `readonly DependencySpec[]`. Currently has 5 entries: showboat, agent-browser, beads, semgrep, bats. Each entry has:\n    51→- `name` (string) — machine identifier\n    52→- `displayName` (string) — human-readable\n    53→- `installCommands` (array of `{ cmd, args }`) — tried in order, first success wins\n    54→- `checkCommand` (`{ cmd, args }`) — used to verify installation\n    55→- `critical` (boolean) — if true, init aborts on failure\n    56→\n    57→### cargo-tarpaulin Entry\n    58→\n    59→```typescript\n    60→{\n    61→  name: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    62→  displayName: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    63→  installCommands: [{ cmd: 'cargo', args: ['install', 'cargo-tarpaulin'] }],\n    64→  checkCommand: { cmd: 'cargo', args: ['tarpaulin', '--version'] },\n    65→  critical: false,\n    66→}\n    67→```\n    68→\n    69→Only one install command — no fallback. `cargo` is the only way to install Rust tools. If `cargo` is missing, the install fails gracefully.\n    70→\n    71→The check command is `cargo tarpaulin --version` (NOT `cargo-tarpaulin --version`). `cargo-tarpaulin` is a cargo subcommand, invoked as `cargo tarpaulin`.\n    72→\n    73→### Unconditional Registry (design note)\n    74→\n    75→The `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` is iterated for ALL projects — there's no stack-conditional filtering in `installAllDependencies()` or `installDeps()`. This means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted even on Node.js/Python projects. Since `cargo` won't exist on non-Rust machines, the install will fail with `status: 'failed'` and continue (because `critical: false`). This matches how `brew install bats-core` fails gracefully on Linux.\n    76→\n    77→If the user wants stack-conditional dependency filtering in the future, that's a separate story. For now, follow the existing unconditional pattern.\n    78→\n    79→### Test Patterns to Follow\n    80→\n    81→In `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`:\n    82→- The `describe('cargo-tarpaulin entry')` block should mirror `describe('semgrep entry')` (line 164) and `describe('bats entry')` (line 222).\n    83→- Use `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY.find(d => d.name === 'cargo-tarpaulin')!` to get the actual spec.\n    84→- The `installAllDependencies` integration tests that enumerate all deps by name (lines 320-353, 438-465) need updated mock implementations to handle `cargo` command.\n    85→\n    86→### Specific Test Updates Required\n    87→\n    88→**Test at line 320 (\"continues when non-critical dep fails\"):**\n    89→The mock implementation checks `cmdStr` for each known command. Add:\n    90→```typescript\n    91→if (cmdStr === 'cargo') throw new Error('not found');\n    92→```\n    93→\n    94→**Test at line 438 (\"prints FAIL and info messages\"):**\n    95→Same pattern — add cargo to the fail list:\n    96→```typescript\n    97→if (cmdStr === 'cargo') throw new Error('not found');\n    98→```\n    99→\n   100→**Test at line 469 (\"contains showboat, agent-browser, beads, semgrep, and bats\"):**\n   101→Add `expect(names).toContain('cargo-tarpaulin')` and update the description string.\n   102→\n   103→**Test at line 479 (\"has exactly 5 entries\"):**\n   104→Change to `expect(DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY).toHaveLength(6)`.\n   105→\n   106→### Do NOT Duplicate\n   107→\n   108→Story 8-3 already:\n   109→- Added `cargo-tarpaulin` detection to `detectCoverageTool()` in `coverage.ts`\n   110→- Added tarpaulin install check via `cargo tarpaulin --version` in coverage detection\n   111→- The dependency registry entry is separate from coverage detection — this is about auto-install during `codeharness init`, not runtime detection\n   112→\n   113→### Architecture Constraints\n   114→\n   115→- **<300 line limit**: `deps.ts` is 175 lines. Adding ~7 lines is fine.\n   116→- **No new npm dependencies**: Uses existing `execFileSync` and types.\n   117→- **NFR5**: Follows existing `DependencySpec` pattern exactly. No type changes.\n   118→\n   119→### Project Structure Notes\n   120→\n   121→- `src/lib/deps.ts` — registry definition and install logic\n   122→- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` — test file (currently 562 lines, adding ~60 lines for new tests)\n   123→- `src/modules/infra/deps-install.ts` — consumer of registry (no changes needed)\n   124→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/deps-install.test.ts` — consumer tests with mocked registry (may need length update in mock)\n   125→\n   126→### References\n   127→\n   128→- [Source: src/lib/deps.ts#DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY L25-75 — existing registry entries]\n   129→- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts#L164-277 — semgrep/bats test patterns to follow]\n   130→- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts#L468-551 — registry shape assertions]\n   131→- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts#L99 — unconditional installDeps call]\n   132→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md#FR13 — requirement]\n   133→\n   134→### Previous Story Intelligence (8-3)\n   135→\n   136→- 8-3 added coverage detection for cargo-tarpaulin. Test suite was at 2980 tests. Zero regressions expected.\n   137→- `vi.mock('node:child_process')` with `importOriginal` was used for ESM-compatible mocking in coverage tests. The deps test file uses a simpler `vi.mock` without `importOriginal` — follow the deps test file pattern.\n   138→- Workspace detection regex `/^\\[workspace\\]/m` in coverage.ts matches the same pattern used in `stack-detect.ts`. Not relevant here but shows consistency approach.\n   139→\n   140→### Git Intelligence\n   141→\n   142→Recent commits: ebaddac (8-3 verified), d6a76bf (8-2 verified), 4c7f498 (8-1 detection).\n   143→All Rust epic stories so far modified: `coverage.ts`, `stack-detect.ts`, `state.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts` + tests.\n   144→This story only touches `deps.ts` and `deps.test.ts` — no overlap with previous stories' files.\n   145→\n   146→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   147→## Verification Requirements\n   148→\n   149→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry.proof.md`)\n   150→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   151→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   152→\n   153→## Documentation Requirements\n   154→\n   155→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   156→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry.md`\n   157→\n   158→## Testing Requirements\n   159→\n   160→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   161→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   162→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   163→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   164→\n   165→## Dev Agent Record\n   166→\n   167→### Agent Model Used\n   168→\n   169→{{agent_model_name_version}}\n   170→\n   171→### Debug Log References\n   172→\n   173→### Completion Notes List\n   174→\n   175→### File List\n   176→\n   177→- `src/lib/deps.ts` — Added cargo-tarpaulin entry to DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY\n   178→- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` — Added cargo-tarpaulin tests, updated registry assertions and installAllDependencies mocks\n   179→- `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — Updated deps.ts description to include cargo-tarpaulin\n   180→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2eefe49-15c3-4418-957c-7920103cee96","uuid":"03bc603c-ad3b-45f5-b590-ddcab38e7ee1","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:32:28.086Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/codeharness-verify-8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry/story.md","content":"# Story 8.4: Register cargo-tarpaulin in dependency registry\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer initializing codeharness on a Rust project,\nI want cargo-tarpaulin to be registered in the dependency registry and auto-installed if missing,\nso that coverage works out of the box without manual setup.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [x] AC1: Given the dependency registry in `src/lib/deps.ts`, when inspected for `cargo-tarpaulin`, then it has `critical: false`, install command `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin`, and check command `cargo tarpaulin --version` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC2: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is not installed and `cargo` is available, when `installDependency()` is called with the cargo-tarpaulin spec, then it runs `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` and verifies installation via `cargo tarpaulin --version` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC3: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is already installed, when `installDependency()` is called with the cargo-tarpaulin spec, then it returns `{ status: 'already-installed' }` without attempting reinstall <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC4: Given `cargo` is not available on the system, when `installDependency()` is called with the cargo-tarpaulin spec, then it returns `{ status: 'failed' }` gracefully (not critical, does not abort init) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [x] AC5: Given `codeharness init` runs on a Rust project where `cargo-tarpaulin` is not installed, when the dependency install phase executes, then it attempts `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` as part of the normal registry iteration <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Add cargo-tarpaulin entry to `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` in `src/lib/deps.ts` (AC: #1)\n  - [x] 1.1 Add new `DependencySpec` object after the `bats` entry\n  - [x] 1.2 Set `name: 'cargo-tarpaulin'`, `displayName: 'cargo-tarpaulin'`\n  - [x] 1.3 Set `installCommands: [{ cmd: 'cargo', args: ['install', 'cargo-tarpaulin'] }]` (single command, no fallback)\n  - [x] 1.4 Set `checkCommand: { cmd: 'cargo', args: ['tarpaulin', '--version'] }`\n  - [x] 1.5 Set `critical: false`\n- [x] Task 2: Update existing tests that assert on registry length (AC: #1)\n  - [x] 2.1 Update `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` length assertion from `5` to `6` in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` line 479\n  - [x] 2.2 Update `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` names assertion to include `'cargo-tarpaulin'` in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` line 469\n  - [x] 2.3 Update any `installAllDependencies` tests that depend on exact registry contents (check mock expectations that enumerate all deps)\n- [x] Task 3: Add cargo-tarpaulin-specific tests in `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [x] 3.1 Add `describe('cargo-tarpaulin entry')` block following semgrep/bats test pattern\n  - [x] 3.2 Test: returns already-installed when `cargo tarpaulin --version` succeeds\n  - [x] 3.3 Test: installs via `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` and returns installed\n  - [x] 3.4 Test: returns failed when `cargo` command not found (graceful failure)\n  - [x] 3.5 Test: cargo-tarpaulin is not critical\n  - [x] 3.6 Test: has single install command via cargo\n  - [x] 3.7 Test: check command is `cargo tarpaulin --version`\n- [x] Task 4: Update `installAllDependencies` test mocks that enumerate deps by name (AC: #4)\n  - [x] 4.1 In the \"continues when non-critical dep fails\" test (~line 320), add mock handling for `cargo` command\n  - [x] 4.2 In the \"prints FAIL and info messages\" test (~line 438), add mock handling for `cargo` command\n- [x] Task 5: Run full test suite — zero regressions\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Registry Structure\n\nThe `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` in `src/lib/deps.ts` (line 25) is a `readonly DependencySpec[]`. Currently has 5 entries: showboat, agent-browser, beads, semgrep, bats. Each entry has:\n- `name` (string) — machine identifier\n- `displayName` (string) — human-readable\n- `installCommands` (array of `{ cmd, args }`) — tried in order, first success wins\n- `checkCommand` (`{ cmd, args }`) — used to verify installation\n- `critical` (boolean) — if true, init aborts on failure\n\n### cargo-tarpaulin Entry\n\n```typescript\n{\n  name: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n  displayName: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n  installCommands: [{ cmd: 'cargo', args: ['install', 'cargo-tarpaulin'] }],\n  checkCommand: { cmd: 'cargo', args: ['tarpaulin', '--version'] },\n  critical: false,\n}\n```\n\nOnly one install command — no fallback. `cargo` is the only way to install Rust tools. If `cargo` is missing, the install fails gracefully.\n\nThe check command is `cargo tarpaulin --version` (NOT `cargo-tarpaulin --version`). `cargo-tarpaulin` is a cargo subcommand, invoked as `cargo tarpaulin`.\n\n### Unconditional Registry (design note)\n\nThe `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` is iterated for ALL projects — there's no stack-conditional filtering in `installAllDependencies()` or `installDeps()`. This means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted even on Node.js/Python projects. Since `cargo` won't exist on non-Rust machines, the install will fail with `status: 'failed'` and continue (because `critical: false`). This matches how `brew install bats-core` fails gracefully on Linux.\n\nIf the user wants stack-conditional dependency filtering in the future, that's a separate story. For now, follow the existing unconditional pattern.\n\n### Test Patterns to Follow\n\nIn `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts`:\n- The `describe('cargo-tarpaulin entry')` block should mirror `describe('semgrep entry')` (line 164) and `describe('bats entry')` (line 222).\n- Use `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY.find(d => d.name === 'cargo-tarpaulin')!` to get the actual spec.\n- The `installAllDependencies` integration tests that enumerate all deps by name (lines 320-353, 438-465) need updated mock implementations to handle `cargo` command.\n\n### Specific Test Updates Required\n\n**Test at line 320 (\"continues when non-critical dep fails\"):**\nThe mock implementation checks `cmdStr` for each known command. Add:\n```typescript\nif (cmdStr === 'cargo') throw new Error('not found');\n```\n\n**Test at line 438 (\"prints FAIL and info messages\"):**\nSame pattern — add cargo to the fail list:\n```typescript\nif (cmdStr === 'cargo') throw new Error('not found');\n```\n\n**Test at line 469 (\"contains showboat, agent-browser, beads, semgrep, and bats\"):**\nAdd `expect(names).toContain('cargo-tarpaulin')` and update the description string.\n\n**Test at line 479 (\"has exactly 5 entries\"):**\nChange to `expect(DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY).toHaveLength(6)`.\n\n### Do NOT Duplicate\n\nStory 8-3 already:\n- Added `cargo-tarpaulin` detection to `detectCoverageTool()` in `coverage.ts`\n- Added tarpaulin install check via `cargo tarpaulin --version` in coverage detection\n- The dependency registry entry is separate from coverage detection — this is about auto-install during `codeharness init`, not runtime detection\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **<300 line limit**: `deps.ts` is 175 lines. Adding ~7 lines is fine.\n- **No new npm dependencies**: Uses existing `execFileSync` and types.\n- **NFR5**: Follows existing `DependencySpec` pattern exactly. No type changes.\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- `src/lib/deps.ts` — registry definition and install logic\n- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` — test file (currently 562 lines, adding ~60 lines for new tests)\n- `src/modules/infra/deps-install.ts` — consumer of registry (no changes needed)\n- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/deps-install.test.ts` — consumer tests with mocked registry (may need length update in mock)\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: src/lib/deps.ts#DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY L25-75 — existing registry entries]\n- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts#L164-277 — semgrep/bats test patterns to follow]\n- [Source: src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts#L468-551 — registry shape assertions]\n- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts#L99 — unconditional installDeps call]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md#FR13 — requirement]\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (8-3)\n\n- 8-3 added coverage detection for cargo-tarpaulin. Test suite was at 2980 tests. Zero regressions expected.\n- `vi.mock('node:child_process')` with `importOriginal` was used for ESM-compatible mocking in coverage tests. The deps test file uses a simpler `vi.mock` without `importOriginal` — follow the deps test file pattern.\n- Workspace detection regex `/^\\[workspace\\]/m` in coverage.ts matches the same pattern used in `stack-detect.ts`. Not relevant here but shows consistency approach.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits: ebaddac (8-3 verified), d6a76bf (8-2 verified), 4c7f498 (8-1 detection).\nAll Rust epic stories so far modified: `coverage.ts`, `stack-detect.ts`, `state.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts` + tests.\nThis story only touches `deps.ts` and `deps.test.ts` — no overlap with previous stories' files.\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry.proof.md`)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n{{agent_model_name_version}}\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n\n- `src/lib/deps.ts` — Added cargo-tarpaulin entry to DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY\n- `src/lib/__tests__/deps.test.ts` — Added cargo-tarpaulin tests, updated registry assertions and installAllDependencies mocks\n- `src/lib/AGENTS.md` — Updated deps.ts description to include cargo-tarpaulin\n","numLines":180,"startLine":1,"totalLines":180}}}
