**Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\",\n   329→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   330→      \"resolved\": false\n   331→    },\n   332→    {\n   333→      \"id\": \"migrated-6\",\n   334→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   335→      \"description\": \"**File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\",\n   336→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   337→      \"resolved\": false\n   338→    },\n   339→    {\n   340→      \"id\": \"migrated-7\",\n   341→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   342→      \"description\": \"**Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\",\n   343→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   344→      \"resolved\": false\n   345→    },\n   346→    {\n   347→      \"id\": \"migrated-8\",\n   348→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   349→      \"description\": \"**ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\",\n   350→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   351→      \"resolved\": false\n   352→    },\n   353→    {\n   354→      \"id\": \"migrated-9\",\n   355→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   356→      \"description\": \"**Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\",\n   357→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   358→      \"resolved\": false\n   359→    },\n   360→    {\n   361→      \"id\": \"migrated-10\",\n   362→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   363→      \"description\": \"**No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\",\n   364→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   365→      \"resolved\": false\n   366→    },\n   367→    {\n   368→      \"id\": \"migrated-11\",\n   369→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   370→      \"description\": \"**HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\",\n   371→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   372→      \"resolved\": false\n   373→    },\n   374→    {\n   375→      \"id\": \"migrated-12\",\n   376→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   377→      \"description\": \"**LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\\\"coverage\\\": \\\"85.5\\\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\",\n   378→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   379→      \"resolved\": false\n   380→    },\n   381→    {\n   382→      \"id\": \"migrated-13\",\n   383→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   384→      \"description\": \"**LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\",\n   385→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   386→      \"resolved\": false\n   387→    },\n   388→    {\n   389→      \"id\": \"migrated-14\",\n   390→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   391→      \"description\": \"**Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\",\n   392→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   393→      \"resolved\": false\n   394→    },\n   395→    {\n   396→      \"id\": \"migrated-15\",\n   397→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   398→      \"description\": \"**Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session.\",\n   399→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   400→      \"resolved\": false\n   401→    },\n   402→    {\n   403→      \"id\": \"migrated-16\",\n   404→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   405→      \"description\": \"**CLI does not expose `runCommand` or `reportFormat` in JSON output.** `codeharness coverage --json` output includes `tool` but not other `detectCoverageTool()` fields. AC1 and AC2 required supplemental verification by replicating function logic from `dist/index.js`. Documentation/API gap.\",\n   406→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   407→      \"resolved\": false\n   408→    },\n   409→    {\n   410→      \"id\": \"migrated-17\",\n   411→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   412→      \"description\": \"**AC4 verified via function replication, not CLI.** `parseTestCounts` is internal and not exercised by any CLI subcommand that accepts raw test output. No `codeharness parse-test-output` command.\",\n   413→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   414→      \"resolved\": false\n   415→    },\n   416→    {\n   417→      \"id\": \"migrated-18\",\n   418→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   419→      \"description\": \"**[OBSERVABILITY GAP]** No log entries in VictoriaLogs during verification. Expected — container doesn't have Docker-in-Docker so observability stack not running inside it.\",\n   420→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   421→      \"resolved\": false\n   422→    },\n   423→    {\n   424→      \"id\": \"migrated-19\",\n   425→      \"story\": \"8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\",\n   426→      \"description\": \"**Workspace aggregation confirmed.** Bundle shows `parseTestCounts` uses global regex with `matchAll`-style loop for multi-crate workspace test output.\",\n   427→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   428→      \"resolved\": false\n   429→    },\n   430→    {\n   431→      \"id\": \"migrated-20\",\n   432→      \"story\": \"8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry\",\n   433→      \"description\": \"**Unconditional dependency registry:** Adding `cargo-tarpaulin` means `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on all projects regardless of stack. Fails gracefully (`critical: false`) but is noisy. Stack-conditional filtering would be a separate story.\",\n   434→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   435→      \"resolved\": false\n   436→    },\n   437→    {\n   438→      \"id\": \"migrated-21\",\n   439→      \"story\": \"8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry\",\n   440→      \"description\": \"**Pre-existing stub overwritten:** The file already existed as a skeleton from sprint planning. Overwritten with comprehensive story as expected.\",\n   441→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   442→      \"resolved\": false\n   443→    },\n   444→    {\n   445→      \"id\": \"migrated-22\",\n   446→      \"story\": \"8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry\",\n   447→      \"description\": \"**Risk: deps-install.test.ts mock registry:** Consumer test mocks `DEPENDENCY_REGISTRY` with hardcoded single-entry array. Mock isolates consumer from registry changes — no update needed there.\",\n   448→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   449→      \"resolved\": false\n   450→    },\n   451→    {\n   452→      \"id\": \"migrated-23\",\n   453→      \"story\": \"8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry\",\n   454→      \"description\": \"**Pre-existing test failures:** 4 tests fail in `modules/sprint/__tests__/state.test.ts` when run as full suite — test isolation issue, not related to this story.\",\n   455→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   456→      \"resolved\": false\n   457→    },\n   458→    {\n   459→      \"id\": \"migrated-24\",\n   460→      \"story\": \"8-4-register-cargo-tarpaulin-dep-registry\",\n   461→      \"description\": \"**Unconditional registry design acknowledged:** `cargo install cargo-tarpaulin` will be attempted on non-Rust projects. `critical: false` handles graceful failure. Stack-conditional filtering deferred.\",\n   462→      \"source\": \"retro\",\n   463→      \"resolved\": false\n   464→    }\n   465→  ]\n   466→}\n   467→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Nb85fbfJGJ6io7c3zpH65E","session_id":"b2eefe49-15c3-4418-957c-7920103cee96","uuid":"779a9d81-0128-4c8b-94a2-9ddc0178af1b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:38:14.275Z"}
